		<div id="comment_body_64230914"><p>Having rules is a consequence of organizing a society of millions of individuals. People usually accept having a government implicitly as described by the concept of the social contract, but we expect something of equivalent value in return for ceding some of our individual autonomy.  The goal is cooperation and mutual benefit, and we should probably consider overthrowing the government if we find it malicious, tyrannical, or ineffective to the point of being not beneficial.</p></div>
	</div>

